    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UE Context Modification Required message encoding in F1AP DU\n\n### Summary\nThe `DU_send_UE_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_REQUIRED` function in the F1AP DU module was causing unexpected behavior when invoked. The function would crash with a segmentation fault when the `cellGroupConfig` field was missing from the RRC information, even though this field should be handled gracefully according to 3GPP specifications.\n\nAdditionally, the error message logged when encoding failed incorrectly stated \"Failed to encode F1 context release request\" instead of the proper \"Failed to encode F1 UE Context Modification Required\", making debugging difficult.\n\nThe root cause was an overly strict `AssertFatal` check that would terminate the program when `cellGroupConfig` was NULL, and the misleading error message that obscured the actual issue.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_ue_context_management.c`: \n  * Replaced `AssertFatal` with a warning log and graceful handling when `cellGroupConfig` is missing\n  * Fixed error message to correctly identify the failed encoding procedure\n  * Added warning when `requestedP_MaxFR1` is used since it's not fully implemented yet\n"
}